# Security Rule

- Never commit secrets, credentials, or service account payloads.
- Do not introduce plaintext logging for encrypted user content.
- Preserve existing E2EE behavior and key-management expectations.
- Keep workflow changes least-privilege; avoid broad permission increases.
- If security posture changes, update docs and clearly describe migration impact.
